      • camelCaseToUnderScore

        protected String camelCaseToUnderScore(String camelCaseName)
        In cassandra, the table/field names are case insensitive and so Java class names and field names have to converted to lower underscored names. Example: CarModel to car_model. firstName to first_name. Limitation. All upper case will not work. Example Dont have a field like CQLStr instead define like CqlStr
